  "text": "Xfz-3 is predominantly expressed from late gastrula stage and restricted to nervous tissue and the pronephros anlage [CITATION_1] . It does not interfere with Wnt-1/wg signaling and early mesoderm differentiation, however, its overexpression inhibits the elongation of the embryo and thus mimics Xwnt-5A effects. There are evidence that Xfz-7 is also mediating the Xwnt-5A pathway (Medina and Steinbeisser, MPI Tubingen, personal communication). It has been cloned independently and found expressed in cranial neural crest, neural tube, eye, heart anlage and pronephric duct (Medina and Steinbeisser, MPI Tu Èbingen, pers. comm.; Gradl, unpublished data: accession number AF114151; [CITATION_2] .",
